<br>
Please try to keep it to flames and suggestions on the ideas and not the people if possible.<br>
<br>
I tried to outline two possible approaches to this spawn.  I want to continually edit this first post to include the feedback most tend to agree with.  After beating on this for a week or so, lets email our recommendation to Verant (and the server GM) on how we would change the quest.  An email could be signed “the Quellious sever” if a large majority agree.  Since a change may never happen, we also need to discuss how to deal fairly with the current quest implementation. <br>
<br>
Option A (the new Verant option):<br>
Three times a day (every day) a L58-60 wraith can spawn randomly in BW that has a 1-2% chance of dropping the container.  Up to 3-6 wraiths can be present at any given time.  This gives a guild the option of determining if the number up is worth changing previous plans for the day.  If your guild wants it bad enough they camp the zone for the weekend with maybe a 20% chance of getting an epic as long as no one else is hunting them.  In this case, it would truly be first come first served FFA due to the random zone loc pop and timers on the mobs.  A group that melee engages the mob first has priority to the mob<br>
<br>
Option B (the Player option):<br>
1.  All the clerics wanting Rage get there approx (6?) hr prior to spawn.<br>
2.  One of the clerics there does a zone shout every 15 min. indicating the countdown to a roll off at (4?) hr prior to spawn.<br>
3. All clerics wanting to roll for Rage must be able to get at least (3?) groups of (L50+? or L55+?) in the zone at (4?) hr prior to the anticipated spawn.<br>
4.  Only one set of (3?) groups can be associated with the roll for one specific cleric.<br>
3.  Roll off determines winner of the upcoming spawn.<br>
4.  The roll winner is the ONLY person that can loot the spawn irregardless of who kills it or how it is killed (to prevent the vulture mentality).  Hopefully, all players in the zone at spawn time will assist the winning cleric in killing the mob.<br>
5.  If the roll winner can’t get it done and the mob despawns then so be it.  Any spectators or other guilds present in the zone can not get priority for the spawn unless the winning cleric verbally passes rights to the spawn in a zone shout.<br>
<br>
Please post comments, suggestions, corrections, or alternate options.  Thank You!<br>
<br>
