<br>
My opinion is you need to concentrate on punishment.  The VI rules are very constraining and the enforcement depends on what is &quot;witnessed by GM or Guide&quot;.  If you want people to play nice on the server then it's time to show them what happens when you or your guild does not &quot;play nice&quot;.<br>
<br>
Are we willing to excommunicate guilds or players?  For example if a guild ninja loots or kill steals something whether or not VI hands down some sort of punishment is the rest of the server population willing to really stick it to the offender.  Suspension is 2 weeks, are willing stop buying items at the bazaar from certain guilds, stop grouping with them, stop ressing, porting, etc.  What happens if you have a friend in that guild are you willing to shun them as well?<br>
<br>
Who is to be the judge?  Are you going to have a court saying X person was right and X person was wrong or just wait for a GM to make that decisioin?<br>
<br>
I know we all want solutions, and it's not even just about Ragefire.  It's about me sitting in EC watching the spam bazaar and people arguing over Orc 1 to the point they need to call GM to arbitrate.<br>
<br>
I don't want to just get to the point where we just throw up our hands and say we give up, but it starts with you.  Yeah sound corny.  But that is how things will get better, when you are willing to back down as a guild or person when something is contested.  That you take the high road and say sure this person might have kill stealed or jumped a spawn or whatever, I'm not going to do that to someone else.  If somoene does wrong and it's clear and cut, they are pariah in my eyes, I won't port, res, or shop from them or people associated with them.  All moralistic crap, but I still believe this is the only way things will get better.<br>
<br>
Anywya, sorry my feedback was not more positive, I'm willing to listen and my guild is willing to follow whatever the server decides just as we did before, but we don't want to be the ones following the rules and when some breaks those rules there better be action just besides us treating a guild as leppers.<br>
