<br>
How would Verant’s current rules apply to this situation?:<br>
1. Ten clerics are in SF waiting for the random pop and those 10 can’t all agree on who should get first shot on Ragefire.  If they do somehow agree, then another 10 clerics long into the zone over the next 2 hrs. and voids any previous negotiation that took place.<br>
2.  Trigger pops and 10 guilds or groups start porting to SF to aid their clerics.<br>
3.  Guild A activates the trigger and starts to pull dragon to their forces.<br>
4.  Guild A decides to kite dragon for 10 min to allow a few more folks to port in.<br>
5.  Under Verant rules, do folks give guild A time to kite cause this is a triggered mob or do Guilds B, C, D, and E see that the dragon is not being actively pulled to a kill force and are ready to pull to their team now? <br>
6.  Guild B takes the kiting aggro away from A cause they are set up with capable force and ready to kill it right now.<br>
7.  Of course guilds C, D, and E were also ready and instead rush the mob with their forces while their pullers ping pong the aggro.<br>
8.  Lets say guilds C, D, and E all engage at about the same time with guild C about 5 seconds before D or E.<br>
9.  Guild D gets the actual kill.<br>
<br>
OK, under Verant rules, who is entitled to the loot and will a GM be able to identify the right winner based on logs after the fact?  What if guild A, B, or C had got the kill?- should that make any difference in who had the priority to kill the mob?  Would the GMs decision on who owns the loot be different depending on who got the actual kill?<br>
<br>
I guess this tread is an attempt to see if anyone wants to try and have discussion on finding a proactive alternative to the many different types of variations of the scenario outlined above.<br>
<br>
OK, I am going to shut up for a while and see if anyone sees any value in continuing this or not.<br>
