<br>
I had a long talk with our server GM (Xeik) about it while I was sitting at the Rage spawn in Skyfire.  Here are a few of the things I learned GM's will consider if the situation is contested.<br>
<br>
1) This camp can be &quot;claimed.&quot;  That is to say, one force given rights to first kill attempt and thereby, rights to the loot if successful.  But it order for it to be claimed, the cleric must have a killing force present during the camp.  If the force dwindles, the cleric will be given a brief period to replenish the force by whatever means within their sphere of influence.  If the force cannot be replenished or the cleric leaves the zone for a reasonable amount of time, the claim is lost.<br>
<br>
2) A single cleric at the camp has no legitimate claim rights as described in #1.<br>
<br>
3) If multiple single clerics are contending for the camp and Ragefire spawns, whichever one who engages Ragefire with killing force first has rights to the kill.  (This is effectively a race to get your people in the zone, to the spawn.)<br>
<br>
4) Kiting does not count as killing force engagement and thus gives no right to the kill.<br>
<br>
5) If one force fails their attempt, they lose their claim and any killing force standing by is entitled to attempt the kill.  If multiple killing forces are standing by, it would be FCFS.<br>
<br>
<br>
Those are the rules the GM's consider when making an arbitration about contention in this spawn, unless Xeik gave me incorrect information.  He also told me him and other server GM's are trying to get this quest changed yet again because of the contention problems.  In the meantime they are working on official rules that can be posted on the official webpage.<br>
<br>
